member.summary: Gets or sets the maximum prefix length of any single allocation in the created allocations. For example, if PrefixLength equals to 30 and AddressCount equals to 5, then the created allocations can be two /30 or one /29 but cannot be three /31 or five /32.

member.summary: Gets or sets a value indicating whether the new allocations should be IP v4.

member.summary: Gets the required tags. They are required to be contained by parent allocation. They can only be unique/inheritable tags.

member.name: P:Microsoft.Azure.Ipam.Contracts.SmartAllocationModel.AdditionalTags
member.summary: Gets the additional tags. They can be any type of tags. For unique/inheritable tags, they are not required to be contained by parent allocation. If contained, the tag value should be the same. If not contained, the tag name and value will be added to the new allocation. For non-unique tags, they will be added to the new allocation directly.

member.summary: Gets the exclusive tags. None of the tags, whatever tag value they have, can be contained by parent allocation. Only tag name will be taken into consideration. They will be added to the new allocation. They can only be unique/inheritable tags.
